III - Comparing magnitudes to reference bands¶

Cross-match the master list to 2MASS to compare magnitudes.

In [10]:
master_catalogue_coords = SkyCoord(master_catalogue['ra'], master_catalogue['dec'])

III.b - Comparing J and K bands to 2MASS¶

The catalogue is cross-matched to 2MASS-PSC withing 0.2 arcsecond. We compare the UKIDSS total J and K magnitudes to those from 2MASS.

The 2MASS magnitudes are “Vega-like” and we have to convert them to AB magnitudes using the zero points provided on this page:

Band Fν - 0 mag (Jy)
J 1594
H 1024
Ks 666.7

In addition, UKIDSS uses a K band whereas 2MASS uses a Ks (“short”) band, this page give a correction to convert the K band in a Ks band with the formula:

$$K_{s(2MASS)} = K_{UKIRT} + 0.003 + 0.004 * (J−K)_{UKIRT}$$
In [11]:
# The AB zero point is 3631 Jy
j_2mass_to_ab = 2.5 * np.log10(3631/1595)
k_2mass_to_ab = 2.5 * np.log10(3631/666.7)
In [12]:
twomass = Table.read("../../dmu0/dmu0_2MASS-point-sources/data/2MASS-PSC_CDFS-SWIRE.fits")
twomass_coords = SkyCoord(twomass['raj2000'], twomass['dej2000'])

idx, d2d, _ = twomass_coords.match_to_catalog_sky(master_catalogue_coords)
mask = (d2d < 0.2 * u.arcsec)

twomass = twomass[mask]
ml_twomass_idx = idx[mask]

nb_compare_mags(twomass['jmag'] + j_2mass_to_ab, master_catalogue['m_video_j'][ml_twomass_idx],
